00:30:26,295 --> 00:30:30,130
I figure they've got to let you out
for your concert, Friday night.

242
00:30:30,417 --> 00:30:33,102
They're beaming it live by satellite
to 85 countries.

243
00:30:33,102 --> 00:30:37,513
Just relax and remember,
there's nothing to worry about.

244
00:31:21,045 --> 00:31:23,059
Amen.

245
00:31:31,305 --> 00:31:33,799
We wish to impress upon you, Mr Rivers,

246
00:31:33,799 --> 00:31:37,442
that we have methods of dealing
with those who will not cooperate.

247
00:31:37,442 --> 00:31:41,277
For the last time,
why did you attack Sergeant Kruger?

248
00:31:41,661 --> 00:31:45,113
I didn't know who it was.
I just saw him pull a gun on a girl.

249
00:31:45,113 --> 00:31:50,674
Might I remind you, Mr Rivers, the penalty
for murder is death by firing squad.

250
00:31:50,674 --> 00:31:54,510
Let us hope for your sake
that Sergeant Kruger survives.

251
00:31:58,729 --> 00:32:01,413
It is the hospital, mein General.

252
00:32:01,413 --> 00:32:05,249
What is the condition of Sergeant Kruger?

253
00:32:05,249 --> 00:32:11,098
I see. Let me know if there
is any change in his condition.

254
00:32:11,673 --> 00:32:13,496
He is dead.

255
00:32:18,098 --> 00:32:21,933
You leave me no alternative,
but to introduce two of my associates.

256
00:32:23,276 --> 00:32:27,111
Bruno is almost blind.
He has to operate wholly by touch.

257
00:32:28,549 --> 00:32:32,385
Klaus is a moron, who knows only what
he reads in "The New York Post".

258
00:32:32,673 --> 00:32:35,741
I believe they never let a man
lose consciousness

259
00:32:35,741 --> 00:32:37,946
however long they may work on him.

260
00:32:37,946 --> 00:32:39,864
You don't scare me.

261
00:32:39,864 --> 00:32:42,837
My manager is on his way
to the American Consulate.

262
00:32:42,837 --> 00:32:45,905
Do not be so sure, Mr Rivers.

263
00:32:45,905 --> 00:32:48,014
Evidently, your friend did not realise

264
00:32:48,014 --> 00:32:51,659
that here in East Germany
we use 220 volt current.

265
00:32:51,659 --> 00:32:55,973
He was found in his hotel room impaled
on a large electrical device.

266
00:32:55,973 --> 00:32:58,082
Our surgeons did what they could

267
00:32:58,082 --> 00:33:02,686
but it took them two hours
just to get the smile off his face.

268
00:33:05,274 --> 00:33:08,246
Perhaps the American
has chosen to reconsider.

269
00:33:18,698 --> 00:33:22,246
Make sure they leave no marks.

270
00:33:44,875 --> 00:33:48,423
Do you know which room
the final chemistry exam is in?

271
00:33:48,423 --> 00:33:51,588
All the exams are over.
Haven't you been to class?

272
00:33:51,588 --> 00:33:54,272
- No.
- But it's the end of the semester.

273
00:33:54,272 --> 00:34:00,122
No, I haven't studied.
Oh no, I'm back in school.

274
00:34:00,122 --> 00:34:02,998
I can't believe I'm back in school.

275
00:34:06,354 --> 00:34:07,792
Thank God.

276
00:34:12,683 --> 00:34:14,217
Well?

277
00:34:14,217 --> 00:34:17,380
They're still working on him.
He won't break.

278
00:34:17,380 --> 00:34:19,778
They've tried everything.

279
00:34:19,778 --> 00:34:22,463
Do you want me to bring out
the LeRoy Neiman paintings?

280
00:34:22,463 --> 00:34:26,298
No. We cannot risk violating
the Geneva Convention.

281
00:34:26,586 --> 00:34:28,696
We'll break him tomorrow.

282
00:35:44,637 --> 00:35:47,323
Who are you?
What are you doing here?

283
00:35:47,323 --> 00:35:50,966
My name is Nick Rivers.
Who are you?

284
00:35:50,966 --> 00:35:56,720
I am Dr Paul Flammond.
I am a prisoner here, just like you.

285
00:35:56,720 --> 00:36:00,171
A year ago, I was close to perfecting

286
00:36:00,171 --> 00:36:03,527
the first magnetic desalinisation process.

287
00:36:03,527 --> 00:36:07,363
So revolutionary,
it was capable of removing the salt

288
00:36:07,459 --> 00:36:11,006
from over 500 million gallons
of sea water a day.

289
00:36:11,006 --> 00:36:14,842
Do you realise what that could mean
to the starving nations of the earth?

290
00:36:17,048 --> 00:36:19,540
They'd have enough salt to last forever.

291
00:36:20,691 --> 00:36:23,471
But then one night,
the Secret Police broke into my house.

292
00:36:23,471 --> 00:36:26,732
They tore me from my family,
ransacked my laboratory

293
00:36:26,732 --> 00:36:29,417
and brought me to this dungeon.

294
00:36:29,417 --> 00:36:31,047
That sucks!

295
00:36:31,047 --> 00:36:33,828
For the first time in my life,

296
00:36:33,828 --> 00:36:38,142
- I am ashamed of being a scientist.
- What do you mean?

297
00:36:38,142 --> 00:36:41,978
They are forcing me to create
a horrible weapon.

298
00:36:42,073 --> 00:36:45,430
- Can't you refuse?
- I wish I could.

299
00:36:45,430 --> 00:36:48,306
But they are holding my daughter.

300
00:36:48,306 --> 00:36:52,621
They'll kill her unless I complete
the Polaris Mine by Sunday.

301
00:36:52,621 --> 00:36:55,978
Sunday? That's Simchas Torah.

302
00:36:55,978 --> 00:36:58,950
And the day the entire NATO
submarine fleet

303
00:36:58,950 --> 00:37:01,347
passes through the Straits of Gibraltar.

304
00:37:01,347 --> 00:37:03,553
Is this the Polaris mine?

305
00:37:03,553 --> 00:37:08,347
Yes. By Sunday I will be able to arm it
with a nuclear warhead.

306
00:37:08,347 --> 00:37:11,702
- How does it work?
- It is a magnetic mine

307
00:37:11,702 --> 00:37:16,114
so powerful it will attract itself
to submarines miles away.

308
00:37:16,114 --> 00:37:19,661
- How about that?
- Oh, no.

309
00:37:26,469 --> 00:37:30,304
Go quickly. If they find out
you've seen this, your life will be worth less

310
00:37:30,400 --> 00:37:33,469
than a truck load of dead rats
in a tampon factory.

311
00:37:42,579 --> 00:37:44,208
Right away.

312
00:37:44,208 --> 00:37:46,989
- Von Horst!
- Ja, mein General.

313
00:37:46,989 --> 00:37:49,961
The government wishes to avoid
an international incident.

314
00:37:49,961 --> 00:37:52,647
Mr Rivers must perform
his concert tonight.

315
00:37:52,647 --> 00:37:55,427
He is to be executed this very minute.

316
00:37:55,427 --> 00:37:59,262
- It'll have to wait. Call them at once.
- Ja, mein General.

317
00:42:25,156 --> 00:42:26,882
Those bikes!

318
00:42:39,730 --> 00:42:42,512
That is no excuse!
Search the road again!

319
00:42:52,772 --> 00:42:54,977
They're in the Eastern sector.

320
00:42:54,977 --> 00:42:57,182
I want the whole area sealed off!

321
00:43:14,058 --> 00:43:16,551
There's a used book store
somewhere around here.

322
00:43:16,551 --> 00:43:18,277
The owner is a member of the Resistance.

323
00:43:18,277 --> 00:43:22,784
- If we can find him...
- Resistance? Wait a minute.

324
00:43:22,784 --> 00:43:27,194
Don't you think it's about time
you told what this is all about?

325
00:43:27,194 --> 00:43:30,359
I'm sorry, I guess I do owe
you an explanation.

326
00:43:30,359 --> 00:43:35,249
Only a year ago I was teaching
a course in black history

327
00:43:35,249 --> 00:43:38,125
at the University of Blaupunkt.

328
00:43:38,125 --> 00:43:43,400
One night, I came home to find my father
had been arrested by the Secret Police.

329
00:43:43,400 --> 00:43:46,564
I've been trying to find him ever since.

330
00:43:47,235 --> 00:43:50,304
Wait a minute. That's Dr Flammond.

331
00:43:50,304 --> 00:43:52,988
I saw him yesterday in Flurgendorf Prison.

332
00:43:52,988 --> 00:43:55,385
Flurgendorf Prison? Is he all right?

333
00:43:55,385 --> 00:43:57,878
- He looks fine.
- Thank God, he's safe.

334
00:43:57,878 --> 00:44:00,947
We must get this information
to the Resistance.

335
00:44:00,947 --> 00:44:04,303
- Maybe they can help us.
- Let's go.

336
00:44:42,466 --> 00:44:47,069
There it is.
It's a Swedish book store.

337
00:45:06,053 --> 00:45:07,588
May I help you?

338
00:45:08,643 --> 00:45:10,848
My father is Dr. Paul Flammond

339
00:45:10,848 --> 00:45:14,587
I'm sorry. I don't know a Dr. Flammond.

340
00:45:15,354 --> 00:45:19,478
He told me you may have a book of
Swedish poems by Von Brieson.

341
00:45:21,587 --> 00:45:24,080
So you are Hillary Flammond!

342
00:45:27,629 --> 00:45:31,368
What can I do for you?

343
00:45:32,327 --> 00:45:34,436
We must speak with "The Torch".

344
00:45:34,436 --> 00:45:36,450
That will be very difficult.

345
00:45:44,312 --> 00:45:46,902
But I will try to arrange it.

346
00:45:47,861 --> 00:45:50,066
Can we leave tonight?

347
00:45:53,997 --> 00:45:56,586
It is too dangerous to travel at night.

348
00:45:59,463 --> 00:46:02,339
You will be taken in the morning
to a potato farm.

349
00:46:02,339 --> 00:46:04,737
Where can we stay tonight?

350
00:46:04,737 --> 00:46:06,559
There is a loft upstairs.

351
00:46:06,559 --> 00:46:08,955
You can use that fire pole.

352
00:46:21,516 --> 00:46:28,037
That's OK. Don't feel bad.
It happens to lots of men the first time.

353
00:46:28,037 --> 00:46:30,146
Just relax. I'll pour you a drink.

354
00:46:30,146 --> 00:46:33,118
We can always try again
in a couple of hours,

355
00:46:33,118 --> 00:46:37,434
she said, as she laid down beside him
and caressed his chest.

356
00:46:37,434 --> 00:46:40,118
Can you believe they print this trash?

357
00:46:40,118 --> 00:46:43,571
Don't worry about it. You were going
to tell me something about your childhood.

358
00:46:45,968 --> 00:46:48,365
When I was a young girl,

359
00:46:48,365 --> 00:46:50,953
my uncle took me on a tropical cruise.

360
00:46:50,953 --> 00:46:52,968
But there was a terrible storm

361
00:46:52,968 --> 00:46:55,365
and the boat sank.

362
00:46:55,365 --> 00:46:57,858
I managed to swim to a deserted island

363
00:46:57,858 --> 00:47:00,254
with a young boy, named Nigel.

364
00:47:00,254 --> 00:47:02,652
Together we had to learn to survive.

365
00:47:05,529 --> 00:47:08,117
Fortunately the ocean provided its bounty,

366
00:47:08,117 --> 00:47:10,994
which Nigel would catch every day.

367
00:47:10,994 --> 00:47:14,063
Later, I would forage inland
for fruit and vegetables

368
00:47:14,063 --> 00:47:18,665
from the endless varieties
of trees and bushes all over the island.

369
00:47:18,665 --> 00:47:22,405
We busied ourselves chopping palm
fronds and lacing them to bamboo

370
00:47:22,405 --> 00:47:24,898
with dried seaweed and snot.

371
00:47:24,898 --> 00:47:28,062
This not only provided us
with a safe haven from the rain.

372
00:47:28,062 --> 00:47:30,938
but sheltered us
from the relentless Santa Ana winds

373
00:47:30,938 --> 00:47:33,815
which would periodically
ravage the island.

374
00:47:33,815 --> 00:47:36,500
The years passed and as we grew up,

375
00:47:36,500 --> 00:47:41,006
we began to notice
strange new feelings awakening in us.

376
00:47:41,006 --> 00:47:43,500
There was no one around to explain this.

377
00:47:43,500 --> 00:47:46,184
We had to learn by ourselves.

378
00:48:14,567 --> 00:48:17,251
Then one day he went fishing.

379
00:48:17,251 --> 00:48:20,704
That was the last I ever saw of Nigel.

380
00:48:20,704 --> 00:48:23,772
I spent months by myself on that island,

381
00:48:23,772 --> 00:48:27,224
until I was finally rescued
by a passing ship.

382
00:48:27,224 --> 00:48:29,813
I'll never forget my feeling of relief.

383
00:48:29,813 --> 00:48:32,018
You can't imagine what it's like

384
00:48:32,018 --> 00:48:34,128
to be separated from your family

385
00:48:34,128 --> 00:48:36,237
at such a young age.

386
00:48:36,237 --> 00:48:37,867
I think I can.

387
00:48:41,415 --> 00:48:46,017
When I was about six years old,
my momma took me to the city.

388
00:48:46,017 --> 00:48:50,525
We went to one of those big old
department stores, and I got lost.

389
00:48:50,525 --> 00:48:53,017
They tried to page her,

390
00:48:53,017 --> 00:48:55,990
but the PA system was on the fritz.

391
00:48:57,044 --> 00:49:00,017
I never saw my momma again.

392
00:49:00,017 --> 00:49:02,798
Some people
from the cosmetics department

393
00:49:02,798 --> 00:49:05,099
fed me a bowl of soup and some bread.

394
00:49:05,099 --> 00:49:07,208
Days stretched into weeks.

395
00:49:07,208 --> 00:49:09,414
One February they got jammed up

396
00:49:09,414 --> 00:49:12,099
during the semi-annual
Lincoln's birthday sale.

397
00:49:12,099 --> 00:49:14,496
They asked me to help out
in Pre-Teen Maternity.

398
00:49:16,797 --> 00:49:19,387
Then one day I overheard
a conversation in personnel

399
00:49:19,387 --> 00:49:22,455
about them needing a new jingle
for their radio ad.

400
00:49:22,455 --> 00:49:26,002
So I picked up my guitar
and I wrote down a tune

401
00:49:26,002 --> 00:49:29,838
that had been mulling and creeping
and crawling around in my head.

402
00:49:30,126 --> 00:49:32,523
It went something like this.

403
00:50:43,670 --> 00:50:45,301
Oh, Nick.

404
00:51:28,258 --> 00:51:30,655
All right, this is it.

405
00:51:30,655 --> 00:51:32,668
I must leave you here.

406
00:51:34,011 --> 00:51:36,217
Go now, quickly.

407
00:51:38,901 --> 00:51:42,161
- Is he all right?
- He caught a cold the other day.

408
00:51:42,161 --> 00:51:44,271
He's just a little hoarse.

409
00:51:44,271 --> 00:51:46,285
Giddy-up, Mario.

410
00:51:57,983 --> 00:52:00,763
- Yes?
- Is this the potato farm?

411
00:52:00,763 --> 00:52:04,983
Yes, I am Albert Potato. Who are you?

412
00:52:04,983 --> 00:52:07,955
We were sent by Sven Jorgensen.

413
00:52:11,886 --> 00:52:13,613
Come this way.

414
00:52:38,926 --> 00:52:42,762
- What do you want?
- We wanna see "The Torch".

415
00:52:43,050 --> 00:52:46,022
No one is allowed to see "The Torch".

416
00:52:46,022 --> 00:52:51,584
But we have important information about
my father, Dr Paul Flammond.

417
00:52:51,584 --> 00:52:54,076
We shall see.

418
00:53:06,637 --> 00:53:09,418
- Nigel!
- Hillary!

419
00:53:15,938 --> 00:53:19,678
It is you. My darling, Hillary.

420
00:53:19,678 --> 00:53:22,555
If only you knew how I've yearned
for this day to come.

421
00:53:22,555 --> 00:53:27,157
Sleepless nights, lonely hours,
hoping, praying that once more

422
00:53:27,157 --> 00:53:30,514
I would gaze
into your ravishing brown eyes.

423
00:53:30,514 --> 00:53:34,157
Who is this I should thank
for bringing you back to me?

424
00:53:34,157 --> 00:53:37,225
This is Nick.
Nick Rivers, he's a friend.

425
00:53:37,225 --> 00:53:41,061
Forgive us, Mr Rivers,
if we have been less than hospitable.

426
00:53:41,349 --> 00:53:47,005
Recently we've had reason to believe
there is a traitor in the Resistance.

427
00:53:47,005 --> 00:53:50,746
Du Quois,
introduce the American to the men.

428
00:53:50,746 --> 00:53:52,376
Very well.

429
00:53:53,143 --> 00:53:59,280
This is Chevalier, Montage, Detente,

430
00:53:59,280 --> 00:54:03,594
Avant Garde, and Déjà Vu.

431
00:54:04,457 --> 00:54:06,950
Have we not met before, Monsieur?

432
00:54:07,909 --> 00:54:09,635
I don't think so.

433
00:54:14,142 --> 00:54:15,771
Over there...

434
00:54:15,771 --> 00:54:20,662
Croissant, Souffle, Escargot,

435
00:54:20,662 --> 00:54:22,963
and Chocolate Mousse.

436
00:54:28,813 --> 00:54:32,264
Now, Mr Rivers,
what is the news that you bring us?

437
00:54:32,264 --> 00:54:35,332
I've seen Dr Flammond
in Flurgendorf prison.

438
00:54:35,332 --> 00:54:38,881
He told me the Polaris mine
will be ready on Sunday.

439
00:54:40,031 --> 00:54:41,182
Sacrebleu.

440
00:54:42,524 --> 00:54:44,825
We'll have to move out tonight.

441
00:54:44,825 --> 00:54:46,935
I'll be back in a moment, my darling.

442
00:54:46,935 --> 00:54:49,141
Prepare the gear for the jump.

443
00:54:49,141 --> 00:54:51,058
Cordon bleu. Zut!

444
00:54:51,058 --> 00:54:53,934
- I want to explain.
- What's to explain?

445
00:54:53,934 --> 00:54:57,387
I'm not the first guy who fell in love
with a girl he met in a restaurant,

446
00:54:57,387 --> 00:55:00,455
who turned out to be the daughter
of a kidnapped scientist,

447
00:55:00,455 --> 00:55:03,811
to lose her to her childhood lover
she'd last seen on a deserted island

448
00:55:03,811 --> 00:55:07,263
who, 15 years later, is the leader
of the French underground.

449
00:55:07,263 --> 00:55:10,427
It all sounds like some bad movie.

450
00:55:17,044 --> 00:55:22,317
Forget it. It'll be better for everyone
if we just forget what's happened.

451
00:55:22,317 --> 00:55:26,153
We've arranged for your safe
transportation across the border tonight.

452
00:55:26,536 --> 00:55:29,796
It's the least we can do
to show our gratitude.

453
00:55:29,796 --> 00:55:34,974
Come, my darling, let me show you
what I've done to the fallout shelter.

454
00:55:56,645 --> 00:55:59,042
Do not take it so hard, Nick.

455
00:55:59,042 --> 00:56:02,301
Life is filled with its little miseries.

456
00:56:02,301 --> 00:56:06,138
Each of us, in his own way,
must learn to deal with adversity

457
00:56:06,329 --> 00:56:09,014
in a mature and adult fashion.

458
00:56:19,753 --> 00:56:23,013
- Mind if I have a swig of this?
- Go right ahead.

459
00:56:23,013 --> 00:56:26,369
- What the hell is this stuff?
- Gasoline.

460
00:56:30,876 --> 00:56:34,712
Don't worry, my darling.
I'm sure your friend will get over it.

461
00:56:34,808 --> 00:56:37,396
He seems a good chap, really.

462
00:56:37,396 --> 00:56:39,889
How wonderful you've returned to me,

463
00:56:39,889 --> 00:56:43,438
when I desperately need you
by my side, to fight for the cause...

464
00:56:43,438 --> 00:56:47,081
- Our cause.
- Oh, Nigel, I am proud of you.

465
00:56:47,081 --> 00:56:51,587
But I'm so confused.
All these years I thought you were dead.

466
00:56:51,587 --> 00:56:54,081
And by all rights I should be.

467
00:56:54,081 --> 00:56:56,670
I floated at sea for days,
nearly unconscious.

468
00:56:56,670 --> 00:56:59,833
Then as luck would have it,
I was picked up by a passing freighter.

469
00:56:59,833 --> 00:57:02,711
I tried to get them to save you too.

470
00:57:02,711 --> 00:57:05,491
It was a foreign ship
and they didn't understand English.

471
00:57:05,491 --> 00:57:10,573
I yelled and screamed, but it only
seemed to excite them all the more.

472
00:57:10,573 --> 00:57:13,738
They took advantage of me
in ways I cannot describe.

473
00:57:13,738 --> 00:57:19,203
Oh, Nigel, it must have been awful.

474
00:57:24,860 --> 00:57:26,682
Latrine!

475
00:57:30,133 --> 00:57:33,586
- What did you find out, Latrine?
- Where are the others?

476
00:57:33,586 --> 00:57:35,504
We never had a chance.

477
00:57:35,504 --> 00:57:37,421
It was a slaughter.

478
00:57:37,421 --> 00:57:40,489
We must put a stop
to these afternoon football games.

479
00:57:40,489 --> 00:57:43,654
- Which direction did they come from?
- Up the road.

480
00:57:45,188 --> 00:57:48,544
- Take cover!
- They're gonna kill us all.

481
00:58:01,777 --> 00:58:03,215
Take this.

482
00:59:06,404 --> 00:59:07,554
Grenade.

483
00:59:19,061 --> 00:59:22,609
We're running out of time.
The plane will not wait for us.

484
00:59:22,609 --> 00:59:24,718
We'll have to make a break for it.

485
00:59:24,718 --> 00:59:27,308
Rendezvous at the cafe
near the landing field.

486
00:59:27,308 --> 00:59:28,362
Wait!

487
00:59:44,758 --> 00:59:46,677
Nice shooting.

488
00:59:46,677 --> 00:59:47,732
My man!

489
01:00:11,990 --> 01:00:14,963
Good. Now everybody's accounted for.

490
01:00:14,963 --> 01:00:18,223
Here's the plan.
We'll be taking off at 1:00 am.

491
01:00:18,223 --> 01:00:20,141
What about the American?

492
01:00:20,141 --> 01:00:22,921
A truck will be here
at exactly midnight.

493
01:00:22,921 --> 01:00:25,894
He'll jump on the back
and be driven on to the border.

494
01:00:25,894 --> 01:00:29,634
Wait. Nick is the only one
who knows the inside of that prison.

495
01:00:32,989 --> 01:00:37,209
Well, Monsieur Rivers,
it seems that you have become,

496
01:00:37,209 --> 01:00:39,989
how do you say, indispensable?

497
01:00:39,989 --> 01:00:41,715
Indispensable.

498
01:00:43,153 --> 01:00:45,264
That's what I thought.

499
01:00:45,264 --> 01:00:49,099
Sorry, fellas. I've done my time
in Flurgendorf prison.

500
01:00:49,195 --> 01:00:51,496
I got a truck to meet.

501
01:00:54,373 --> 01:00:58,208
Nick, ask any price you want,
but you must help us.

502
01:00:58,208 --> 01:01:02,043
Seems as long as I know my way
around that prison, I'll never be lonely.

503
01:01:02,331 --> 01:01:04,441
I know how you feel about me.

504
01:01:04,441 --> 01:01:07,605
But put your feelings aside
for something more important.

505
01:01:07,605 --> 01:01:11,056
Like what a great cause
you and Nigel are fighting for?

506
01:01:11,056 --> 01:01:14,221
- But this was your cause too.
- My only cause is my music.

507
01:01:14,221 --> 01:01:16,331
That's exactly what I mean.

508
01:01:16,331 --> 01:01:21,316
Didn't you see the eyes of those kids
at your concert? You must help us.

509
01:01:21,316 --> 01:01:23,618
If not for me, for the cause of freedom.

510
01:01:25,919 --> 01:01:27,453
Latrine.

511
01:01:28,700 --> 01:01:32,535
- A traitor in our midst.
- Well done, Latrine.

512
01:01:32,631 --> 01:01:35,604
I see you have dealt with him
appropriately.

513
01:01:35,604 --> 01:01:37,521
Not the bird, you fool!

514
01:01:37,521 --> 01:01:41,356
This is a carrier pigeon on its way
to German headquarters.

515
01:01:41,452 --> 01:01:44,042
Look, a message.

516
01:01:44,042 --> 01:01:49,603
Resistance planning to free Flammond,
Sunday, 8:00 am.

517
01:01:49,603 --> 01:01:54,014
That means the traitor
is someone at this very table.

518
01:01:59,959 --> 01:02:04,657
Excuse me, aren't you Nick Rivers,
the American rock and roll star?

519
01:02:06,383 --> 01:02:08,301
No, I'm not.

520
01:02:08,301 --> 01:02:11,465
But you must be.
Won't you sing us one song?

521
01:02:11,465 --> 01:02:14,342
I'm sorry. You must have me confused
with somebody else.

522
01:02:14,342 --> 01:02:17,602
I'm Mel Torme.

523
01:02:22,397 --> 01:02:24,122
That was close.

524
01:02:24,122 --> 01:02:27,958
- Perhaps a bit too close.
- What do you mean?

525
01:02:27,958 --> 01:02:31,794
We have no proof
that this man is who he claims to be.

526
01:02:31,889 --> 01:02:35,725
Yet we're asking him to lead us into
Germany's most heavily guarded prison.

527
01:02:36,012 --> 01:02:39,560
- That's absurd!
- Just a moment, my darling.

528
01:02:39,560 --> 01:02:41,862
He came to us with no credentials.

529
01:02:41,862 --> 01:02:45,697
The Germans never knew the location
of our headquarters, until he arrived.

530
01:02:45,984 --> 01:02:48,477
And we've been
infiltrated by a traitor.

531
01:02:48,477 --> 01:02:51,163
Nigel, what are you saying?

532
01:02:52,217 --> 01:02:55,669
How do we know
he's not Mel Torme?

533
01:03:08,230 --> 01:03:10,436
Look, he's at the jukebox.

534
01:05:09,239 --> 01:05:11,157
This is not Mel Torme.

535
01:05:39,060 --> 01:05:40,690
Oh, Nick.

536
01:05:43,087 --> 01:05:44,622
Yes?

537
01:05:44,622 --> 01:05:48,265
We don't know
what's going to happen down there.

538
01:05:48,265 --> 01:05:52,771
This may be the last time I'll see you.
There's something I wanted to say.

539
01:05:52,771 --> 01:05:55,553
- You don't have to say anything.
- But I want to.

540
01:05:55,553 --> 01:05:57,758
You must know that when we were
together last night,

541
01:05:57,758 --> 01:06:00,442
I had no idea that Nigel
was still alive.

542
01:06:00,442 --> 01:06:02,647
And now that you know?

543
01:06:04,182 --> 01:06:07,538
Oh, Nick, his work is so important to him.

544
01:06:07,538 --> 01:06:12,715
I must stay with him.
He pleaded with me not to leave.

545
01:06:12,715 --> 01:06:17,031
I just hope you realise
that's all he means to me.

546
01:06:17,031 --> 01:06:20,483
Oh, I don't know what's right any longer.

547
01:06:24,223 --> 01:06:27,578
I only wish I didn't love you so much.

548
01:07:12,166 --> 01:07:14,467
I've spotted the herd.

549
01:07:14,467 --> 01:07:16,960
They're the key to the whole plan.

550
01:07:16,960 --> 01:07:19,644
Now, we're here.

551
01:07:21,755 --> 01:07:23,576
Every morning at 7:15

552
01:07:23,576 --> 01:07:26,932
the prison guards bring the cows
from here, up this road

553
01:07:26,932 --> 01:07:29,712
towards the prison
for their morning milking.

554
01:07:29,712 --> 01:07:33,453
Du Quois and I will merge
with the herd here.

555
01:07:33,453 --> 01:07:38,438
And sneak in through the gate
in the electrified fence.

556
01:07:38,438 --> 01:07:40,932
Then we'll break away from the other cows

557
01:07:40,932 --> 01:07:43,233
and enter the generator building here.

558
01:07:43,233 --> 01:07:47,835
At exactly 7:25 we cut the power.

559
01:07:47,835 --> 01:07:51,671
The rest of you come through here,
scale this wall,

560
01:07:51,959 --> 01:07:54,452
and Nick can lead you to Flammond's cell.

561
01:07:54,452 --> 01:07:57,807
Meanwhile, Hillary will steal this truck
by the railway crossing

562
01:07:57,807 --> 01:08:00,972
and pick us up back here.
Then we drive to the landing field

563
01:08:00,972 --> 01:08:03,561
where the plane will be waiting for us.
Let's go.

564
01:08:16,505 --> 01:08:19,383
No, you take the head.
I'm taking the back.

565
01:08:19,383 --> 01:08:21,492
- But the plan was...
- Forget it.

566
01:08:21,492 --> 01:08:25,135
I give the orders.
Shut up and give me the back half.

567
01:08:25,135 --> 01:08:28,203
All right, be an asshole.

568
01:08:37,696 --> 01:08:40,573
- Here they come.
- OK, let's move out.

569
01:08:46,709 --> 01:08:49,203
All right, let's go. Double time.

570
01:08:58,024 --> 01:09:01,860
We only have five minutes to get
to the circuit box and throw the switch.

571
01:09:02,148 --> 01:09:05,120
We've got to hurry.
Can you see the gate?

572
01:09:05,120 --> 01:09:08,668
- Yes, it's just ahead.
- Where are the guards?

573
01:09:08,668 --> 01:09:11,449
I can only see one.

574
01:09:11,449 --> 01:09:13,846
There girl, move along.

575
01:09:21,229 --> 01:09:23,818
Stay behind the guards.

576
01:09:23,818 --> 01:09:27,366
Once we're round the corner
we'll break away from the herd.

577
01:09:27,366 --> 01:09:29,284
OK, now!

578
01:09:31,201 --> 01:09:32,735
I think we did it.

579
01:09:36,474 --> 01:09:40,790
- Can you see the generator?
- It's behind the feed bin.

580
01:09:40,790 --> 01:09:43,379
All right, let's go. We've got to hurry.

581
01:09:44,433 --> 01:09:46,159
Mon Dieu!

582
01:09:51,529 --> 01:09:54,501
Nigel, you OK?

583
01:09:54,501 --> 01:09:56,324
Oh, yeah.

584
01:09:56,324 --> 01:09:58,241
Let's go.

585
01:09:58,241 --> 01:10:02,939
What's the hurry? Why are you always
in such a bloody rush?

586
01:10:02,939 --> 01:10:06,008
I just wanted to take a...rest.

587
01:10:23,747 --> 01:10:27,295
- The guards have passed.
- How long till they cut the power?

588
01:10:27,295 --> 01:10:29,980
Three more minutes.

589
01:10:29,980 --> 01:10:32,185
Then we can cut the wire.

590
01:10:55,774 --> 01:10:57,787
There it is.

591
01:11:44,867 --> 01:11:46,114
Lovely.

592
01:12:01,263 --> 01:12:03,278
You're all right now. I'm here.

593
01:12:04,141 --> 01:12:05,962
It's all right.

594
01:12:12,099 --> 01:12:13,538
Hey.

595
01:12:32,044 --> 01:12:33,098
Here, here.

596
01:12:40,193 --> 01:12:42,112
Vive la France!

597
01:12:56,111 --> 01:12:58,699
- Nigel, what are you doing?
- Never you mind.

598
01:12:58,699 --> 01:13:01,193
Why do you want to go back
to the meter shed?

599
01:13:01,193 --> 01:13:05,028
- We're turning the power back on.
- But that will set off the alarms.

600
01:13:05,316 --> 01:13:07,905
- The others will be trapped. I refuse!
- Oh?

601
01:13:09,534 --> 01:13:12,891
This gun says you won't.
Now, move.

602
01:13:12,891 --> 01:13:17,589
So, it is you who is the traitor!

603
01:13:32,260 --> 01:13:36,671
Don't take it too badly.
You're no more a fool than the others.

604
01:13:36,671 --> 01:13:39,452
Now, get over there and...

605
01:13:47,985 --> 01:13:50,575
- We're taking you out of here.
- But my daughter.

606
01:13:50,575 --> 01:13:53,068
Don't worry. Hillary's with us.

607
01:13:53,068 --> 01:13:55,752
Thank God, but how ironic.

608
01:13:55,752 --> 01:13:59,588
Another day and I would have
completed my tunnel.

609
01:14:06,204 --> 01:14:07,835
Nice work.

610
01:14:30,847 --> 01:14:32,093
Nigel.

611
01:14:32,093 --> 01:14:34,203
Very clever, my darling.

612
01:14:34,203 --> 01:14:36,888
You've put the pieces together
very nicely,

613
01:14:36,888 --> 01:14:40,436
but unfortunately it's too late
for you and the others.

614
01:14:40,436 --> 01:14:44,271
- But how could you?
- It wasn't difficult.

615
01:14:44,271 --> 01:14:47,436
I could have returned to rescue you
from that wretched island,

616
01:14:47,436 --> 01:14:50,600
but it would have meant leaving
my new found comrades.

617
01:14:50,600 --> 01:14:52,517
Comrades?

618
01:14:53,476 --> 01:14:56,545
Yes, it was a Russian ship.

619
01:14:56,545 --> 01:14:59,901
They taught me all about you...
Imperialist swine.

620
01:14:59,901 --> 01:15:03,736
I was exposed to the works
of great thinkers. Karl Marx, Lenin,

621
01:15:03,927 --> 01:15:06,134
L Ron Hubbard, Freddie Laker.

622
01:15:06,134 --> 01:15:09,777
Now get in the truck.
We're going for a ride.

623
01:15:33,556 --> 01:15:35,762
Something's wrong. Where's the truck?

624
01:15:35,762 --> 01:15:37,680
- Where's Hillary?
- I'm hungry.

625
01:15:45,159 --> 01:15:47,077
What happened?

626
01:15:48,227 --> 01:15:51,871
Nigel made me go back to the meter shed.

627
01:15:51,871 --> 01:15:54,556
He ordered me to set off the alarm.

628
01:15:55,611 --> 01:15:58,871
And what does he want us to do now?

629
01:15:58,871 --> 01:16:01,459
Nothing, you numbskull, Nigel's the traitor.

630
01:16:28,596 --> 01:16:30,321
Latrine!

631
01:16:32,431 --> 01:16:36,267
Nigel took Hillary in the truck. That way.

632
01:16:36,363 --> 01:16:39,335
I cannot leave the country
without my daughter.

633
01:16:39,335 --> 01:16:42,883
I'm going after them.
I'll meet you at the landing field.

634
01:16:42,883 --> 01:16:45,088
Nick, whether you make it back or not,

635
01:16:45,088 --> 01:16:48,732
that plane must take off
with Dr Flammond at 18:00.

636
01:16:48,732 --> 01:16:52,087
But we recommend you be there
at least 45 minutes before departure,

637
01:16:52,087 --> 01:16:54,389
especially at this time of year.

638
01:16:54,389 --> 01:16:57,170
- Good luck, Nick.
- Let's go.

639
01:16:57,170 --> 01:16:58,704
Good luck.

640
01:17:07,238 --> 01:17:11,073
You've go to hand it to the Germans,
they make great cars.

641
01:19:33,657 --> 01:19:35,670
Goodbye.

642
01:20:05,107 --> 01:20:07,984
There's no more time.
We've got to take off now.

643
01:20:07,984 --> 01:20:10,190
I will not leave without my daughter.

644
01:20:10,190 --> 01:20:13,066
Listen, old chap,
in a few minutes it'll be dawn

645
01:20:13,066 --> 01:20:16,614
and we'll be sitting ducks
to their anti-aircraft guns.

646
01:20:16,614 --> 01:20:18,628
There they are!

647
01:20:23,134 --> 01:20:26,299
Oh, Father. Thank God, you're safe.

648
01:20:26,299 --> 01:20:29,271
How I feared I would never see you again.

649
01:20:29,271 --> 01:20:31,668
I am so proud of you, my beloved.

650
01:20:31,668 --> 01:20:35,312
There'll be time to talk on the plane.
You'd better hurry.

651
01:20:35,312 --> 01:20:38,476
- But I can't go on that plane.
- But Hillary!

652
01:20:38,476 --> 01:20:43,078
I'm needed here. For as long
as a single man is forced to cower

653
01:20:43,078 --> 01:20:45,189
under the iron fist of oppression,

654
01:20:45,189 --> 01:20:47,298
as long as a child cries out in the night,

655
01:20:47,298 --> 01:20:51,612
or an actor can be elected president,
we must continue the struggle.

656
01:20:51,612 --> 01:20:53,050
No, Hillary.

657
01:20:53,050 --> 01:20:56,024
It is too dangerous for you
in Germany, now.

658
01:20:56,024 --> 01:20:59,092
Yes, go with Nick. Don't worry about us.

659
01:20:59,092 --> 01:21:01,776
We will hear his music
on the "Voice of America".

660
01:21:01,776 --> 01:21:05,612
We will hear it in the hearts of people,
and in elevators everywhere.

661
01:21:05,900 --> 01:21:09,735
And as long as we do,
we know we are not alone in our fight.

662
01:21:10,023 --> 01:21:13,571
They're right, Hillary.
And when we get to America...

663
01:21:13,571 --> 01:21:16,927
- Who knows what will be then.
- Everything will be fine.

664
01:21:16,927 --> 01:21:22,583
Things change, people change,
hairstyles change...

665
01:21:22,583 --> 01:21:24,598
I want you to be with me.

666
01:21:24,598 --> 01:21:28,433
Interest rates fluctuate. Who knows?

667
01:21:28,529 --> 01:21:32,364
Don't you want to come with me?
If you don't, say it now.

668
01:21:32,653 --> 01:21:37,734
Want!
Want more than anything!

669
01:21:37,734 --> 01:21:40,610
Take me. Take me with you!

670
01:21:53,268 --> 01:21:57,582
Goodbye, Chocolate Mousse.
I'll never forget you.

671
01:21:57,582 --> 01:22:01,226
Goodbye, Du Quois.
Take care of yourself.

672
01:22:02,569 --> 01:22:06,404
Goodbye, Déjà Vu.
I will always remember you.

673
01:22:06,500 --> 01:22:10,239
And I'll miss you, most of all, Scarecrow.